DIALOG::
A::Hi Dear, how did the mouse get away from the Lion?
B::The mouse offered a good deal to the lion.
A::What type of deal?
B::The mouse said that he may repay the lion's kindness in the future.
A::Did the lion accept the deal?
B::Yes, The lion felt that Mouse's words were amusing.
A::Did the mouse have a chance to pay the lion back?
B::Of course, the mouse gnawed away the ropes to free the lion. 
A::What is the moral of the story?
B::Small acts of kindness will be rewarded greatly.

